                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "rHIlY",
                  "name": "ReviewCard",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "fill": "#FFFFFF",
                  "cornerRadius": 16,
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 12,
                  "padding": 24,
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "DKAfP",
                      "name": "reviewTitle",
                      "fill": "#2A3D22",
                      "content": "Review",
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 16,
                      "fontWeight": "700"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "Zfc1c",
                      "name": "reviewText",
                      "fill": "#4A5A38",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Filosofi Kopi BDG is one of those places that gets everything mostly right. The space is airy and calm, with just enough natural light filtering through large windows to make working here feel productive but not sterile. Coffee quality is solid — the single origin pour-over was clean and well-extracted, and the pricing lands comfortably in the Bandung range.\n\nThe vibe leans literary and unhurried. You won't be rushed, and tables are spaced out enough that laptop work doesn't feel awkward. WiFi held up well during my two-hour session. On the quieter side — I'd rate the noise level around 2/5 on a Tuesday afternoon. Parking was the one friction point: street parking fills up fast and the nearby spots can be a walk.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.7,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 13,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    }
                  ]
                },
